            <h3>Ideation</h3>
                <p>
                        Design Goals:  Creating touching points beyond users’ expectations
                </p>
            <img src="/images/showcase/ideation.png" width="30%" margin="40px 0"> 
            <p>
                Under what circumstances does the user use the search engine instead of the APP to check the weather?  </br>
            <b>Advantages of Search Engine</b> </br>
                · Accumulation of user data enables the search engine to know what the user’s final goal is when they check the weather. </br>
                · The search form of  text encourages users to ask detailed questions. </br>
                · The SERP page can be a more flexible form of presentation than the app, and it can even do different things for each person.   </br>
            </p>
        </div>  
        <div class="paragraph">
                <h3>Assumption</h3>
                <p>
                        · Users typically use search engines when they want to know the weather in other places in the next few days because of <b>travel plans</b>.</br>
                        · When the user only wants to know the current outdoor weather, the mobile app can also provide the user with the information they need in a more convenient way.</br>
                        · The advantage of the search engine in <b>mastering user information</b> can be embodied in the form of a <b>personal assistant</b>.</br>
                        · Different users need different suggestions even under the same weather conditions.
                </p>
